    "body": "> Syntactic sugar is a compelling reason. also it makes the language feel consistent and familiar to newcomers from any C style language.\n\nAnd that's an horror and lead to some misunderstanding. How many people knows the difference between:\n\n``` c\nint i = 0;\n\nwhile (i++ < 10);\n```\n\nand:\n\n``` c\nint i = 0;\n\nwhile (++i < 10);\n```\n\nAlso, like said above, `i++` returns a value whereas `i += 1` doesn't.\n",
