    "body": "It becomes even uglier when you need to combine it with wrapping integer operations. Consider for instance this getter for a primitive ringbuffer I am trying to prettify at the moment:\r\n```rust\r\nfn get(&mut self) -> Option<u8> {                   \r\n  if self.head == self.tail { return None; }       \r\n  self.tail = self.tail.wrapping_add(1);           \r\n  Some(self.data[self.tail.wrapping_sub(1) & MASK])\r\n}                                                  \r\n```\r\nThis is much noisier than the equivalent C\r\n```C\r\nint get(*buf b)\r\n{\r\n  if (b->head == b->tail) return -1;\r\n  return b->data[b->tail++ & MASK];\r\n}\r\n```",
