    "body": "> I would've voted for a method called `post_increment()` on integer types. It's still shorter than doing `{ let y = x; x += 1; y }`\r\n\r\nBut below example cannot run: @norcalli \r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut x = 2134;\r\n    // simulate: console.log(x, ++x);\r\n    println!(\"{}, {}\", x, {let y = x; x += 1; y} );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n[Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=84cd34383701b0a200a5158f01367807)\r\n\r\n",
